Business Brief -- Helionetics Inc.:
   Break-Even 1991 Results
   Are Expected by Concern
For the 1992 first quarter, Helionetics expects to report
a significant increase in operating profit from the $190,000
reported in the same period last year. Revenue was about $5
million, versus $2.7 million a year ago.
   The company is involved in applications of laser
technology, computer graphics and electric power conditioning
products. Its stock dropped 37.5 cents on the news to $7.625
on the American Stock Exchange.